<Author>Georgeene
<Content>Paper Thin Walls - Not good if you value sleep Just returned from Barcelona - cold but amazing place, buildings, shops and food excellent. Our travel agent suggested Hotel Balmes as we could not get availability in Gravina. We looked at reviews on Trip Advisor and they seemed Ok for went for it.This is 3 star and there are good and very bad points depending on your priorities.Our first experience was not the best as we advanced booked a double non-smoking room. When we checked they tried to sell us an upgrade to an executive room for an extra E20 per night, but we did not feel it was necessary. When were taken up to the room it was a twin and stank, I mean stank of smoke. They did not inform us of this when we checked in, but told me when I went to check - they told me were fully booked, no apology - even though they had already offered an alternative executive room!, which as this was their mistake seemed poor and their attitude was totally indifferent. So we slept in it and thank god were moved the next day (or at least we though it would be better).GOOD POINTS- Breakfast great, times good and lots of choice and nice waitresses.- Location excellent for exploring sights, metro, nice shops and restaurants. - Hotel spotless.- Free internet access if you can get on it as only 1 PC.BAD POINTS- The walls are paper thin 鈥?we could hear every cough and movement in all the surrounding rooms of which there seemed to be many at every corner of the hotel. We had our fair share of noise some well into and in the middle of the early hours but I dread to think if you got someone who snored next door - then God help you! We thought it was just a one off the 1st night in the smoke room but the noise problem was inherent in the hotel structure as there are clearly no cavities between the rooms. If you are a person who likes sleep 鈥?you should AVOID this hotel.- Reception staff could not care less, they did not even say hello when we went in and out of the hotel, it was clear they were not happy in their work!Having said apart from the fact we were quite tired as did not get great sleep Barcelona is fantastic and Hotel Omm is a must for a relaxing drink after dinner. 
