<Content>How could you not be happy here ? We have just come back from 6 days in room 520. Ok, so the rooms are hardly suite size, but they're hardly small either. All I can imagine is that the less satisfied reviewers on here are used to staying in 5* suites. My top 10 points about the hotel:1) Fab location 30 minutes gentle ramble from the Ramblas/Port Vell; well situated for the Passeig de Gracia (for glam desginer window shopping) and the Rambla de Catalunya (Ciudad Central having the best tapas in town). 2) Nice bathrooms with GREAT water pressure and foot-washing basins. 3) V expensive mini-bars can be emptied and refilled with your personal supermarket buys.4) Nice little pool ideal for cooling off with sunloungers and towels5) Decent brekkie spread with sausages, cured meats, bread, cereals, pastries and fresh fruits. 6) Free early morning tea and coffee (but only till 0730) 7) Huge beds - over king sized which are very comfy. 8) Safe for your valuables (which you don't have to pay extra for)9) Nice sized room with pleasant view over the gardens, little dining/lounge area10) Interesting egyptian artifacts all over the hotelAll in all a very pleasant experience, with none of the niggles mentioned in the previous reviews. 
